# Lecture 2

## 3 levels of culture
* populatr/mass
  * Mass Produced
  * known author
  * Examples
    * LOTR
    * Star Wars
  
* elite
  * education
  * training
  * cost
  * Examples
    * horseback riding
    * fine art

* folk
  * local
  * tradition
  * oral history
  * Examples
    * Dia de los muertos
    * Tattoos
    * Skateboarding

* Many types of culture fall into or are partially multiple levels

## Folklore
Folklore is the dynamic process of conveying informal knowledge and culture

mass media ofter incorrectly uses the term to mean false, old, or quaint

### NOT folklore
* single author
* formal knowledge
* no roots in tradition
  
## Regional folklore and cultural competence

### Framing Questions
    1. How do we define regional folklore?
    2. what are the key aspects of cultural competence?
    3. how does culture shape how we see place?

* Regional Folklore
  * informal culture that tells us something about a place (also people and time period)
  * Wulver
    * shetland island variant of the werewolf
    * much more tame than the traditional werewolf
    * likes to fish
    * leaves fish on the doorsteps of neighbors
    * it is a common theme to take scary creatures and make them softer(see twilight)
  * this class views folklore through magical creatures and ritual
  
* Cultural Competence
  * Fieldwork Protocol
  * Checklist in reading Pg 38-39
    * Prepare
      * Research
    * Field approach
      * Humility
      * informed consent, listen(more than talk)
      * Hold off judgement
    * Analyze
      * Patterns
      * Cite evidence
      * Earned conclusions

* Place Through Individual/ cultural lenses
  * Varieties of Maps, Directions, Economics, Tourism, Demographics, Flora & Fauna
  * Place as Cultural and Individual
    * World Building